quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  18,98,"He said: this is a mercy from my Lord; then when the promise of my Lord cometh, He shall make it powder, and the promise of my Lord is ever true"
  18,99,"And We shall leave them on that day surging one against anot her and the trumpet shall be blown, and then We shall assemble them together"
  18,100,And We shall set hell on that Day unto the infidels with a setting
  18,101,"Unto those whose eyes had been under a covering from My remembrance, nor had they been able to hear"
  18,102,"Deem then those who disbelieve that they may take My bondmen, instead of Me, as patrons! Verily We have gotten ready the Hell for the infidels as an entertainment"
  18,103,"Say thou: shall I declare unto you the greatest losers in respect of works"
  18,104,"They are those whose effort is wasted in the life of the world, and they deem that they are doing well in performance"
  18,105,"They are those who disbelieve in the signs of their Lord and in the meeting with Him; so of non-effect will be made their works, and We shall not allow them on the Day of Judgment any weight"
  18,106,That shall be their meed--Hell-for they disbelieved and held My revelations and My apostles in mockery
  18,107,"Verily those who believe and do righteous works, unto them shall be gardens of Paradise for an entertainment"
  18,108,"As abiders therein, they shall not seek therefrom any change"
  18,109,"Say thou: were the sea to become ink for the words of my Lord, the sea would surely exhaust ere the words of my Lord exhausted, even though We brought onot her like thereof for support"
  18,110,"Say thou: I am but a human being like yourselves; revealed unto me is that your God is One God. Whosoever then hopeth for the meeting with his Lord, let him work righteous work, and let him not associate in the worship of his Lord anyone"